Creating the Map

My goal was to split up the universities by state, so weâ€™ll take a slightly different approach to creating the map.

Letâ€™s load leaflet and create the base map.

map <- addTiles(leaflet())

Now weâ€™ll add our data by state. Weâ€™ll also attach a hyperlink to each college so that we can visit its website quickly.

for (st in unique(data$STABBR)) {
  map <- map %>% addMarkers(data = data[data$STABBR == st,],
                            lat = ~LATITUDE, lng = ~LONGITUDE,
                            clusterOptions = markerClusterOptions(),
                            label = ~INSTNM, group = st,
                            
                            popup = ~paste("<b><a href='http://", INSTURL,     # the university website
                                           "' target='_blank'>", INSTNM,       # opens in a new page.
                                           "</a></b><br />", CITY, ", ",       # the university city, st
                                           STABBR, sep = ""))                  # shows below it.
}

Finally, letâ€™s add a layers control so that we can choose to look at only the colleges we care about.

  options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = FALSE)
